race.comment: STORMY'S SHOW (8) looks an exciting prospect on resumption. She comes into this without a trial, but she showed good ability in her debut campaign and this doesn't look an overly strong CL2. Has the speed to cross from out wide and can return on a winning note. CHERYL'S SHOUT (7) is building nicely this time in work, finishing 1.5L off the winner at Belmont last start in a CL3. This is easier than what she tackled last start and the inside draw should see her get every chance. Third-up now and can put his best foot forward. ROUNDABOUT GLORY (2) will be fitter for two trials coming into this and he's a first-up winner in the past. The claim of Nottle is a big tick and she has options from a middle barrier. Can put his best foot forward. WINEACLOCKSUMWHERE (1) can resume on a positive note with Faithfull in the saddle. DASHING ERIKA (3) looks well placed first-up and can be in the finish on resumption.
